
<body>
    <%= render "dash_banner" %>
    <%= render "dash_welcome_modal" %>
     <div class="intro_wrapper">
        <div class="intro_button welcome_dash_intro" onclick="javascript:introJs().start();" onclick="javascript:introJs().goToStep(3).start();" data-step="7" data-intro="Use this button to Launch this intro anytime." data-position="left">?</div>
    </div>

    <center>
        <div id="welcome_msg">
            <h2>Welcome Back!</h2>
        </div>
        <div id="prayers_per_week" data-intro="<p><strong>Salah Adherence:</strong><br/> Salah adherence measures the percent of time you pray each salah. (ex. If you miss Maghrib every second day, you have a 50% adherence for Maghrib)</p>" data-step="1" data-position="top">
            <%= render "overall_data" %>
        </div>
        <%= render "line_graph" %>

        <%= render "performance_summary" %>
        <div class="chart_data_container">
        <%= render "back_graph" %>
        <%= render "main_chart" %>
        </div>

        <div id="overall_analytics">
            <table id="table_of_analytics">
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td class="analytics_cells" data-intro="<p><strong>Current Average:</strong><br/> This graph visually shows your current daily average. Your daily average uses the last 15 days (or less) of your Salah counts to get the average. <strong>Longest Streak</strong> shows the longest consecutive number of days you prayed all 5 Salawat</p>" data-step="4" data-position="top">
                            <%= render "user_average" %>
                        </td>
                        <td width="450px" class="analytics_cells" data-intro="<p><strong>Day of the Week Average:</strong><br/> This chart shows you a unique average for each day of the week. We indivisually measure your Salah count for each day and average it over the number of times that day was tracked. This way, we can easily highlight the days with the best & worst average week over week. Take a look at your worst day'schedule and try to find ways to incorporate Salah in the schedule. This will help you improve your overall average.</p>" data-step="5" data-position="top">
                            <%= render "weekday_prayer_data" %>
                        </td>
                        <td class="analytics_cells" data-intro="<p><strong>Missed Salahs:</strong><br/> This graph shows you the total Salawat you you've missed, broken down by each specific Salah.<br/> Fard Salah are obligatory to make-up. Use this counter to slowly make-up for each of your missed Salawat. This won't improve your average, but it will help you a lot in answering the ultimate question on the Day of Judgement</p>" data-step="6" data-position="top">
                            <%= render "missed_prayers" %>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </center>
    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
    <%= render "footer" %>
</body>
<script type="text/javascript">
    if(<%= @show_intro %>) {   
        $("#welcomeDashModal").modal("show");
    }
    $(".view_dash_welcome").on("click", function() {
        $("#welcomeDashModal").modal("hide");
    })
</script>
